# Rasm Materials

Read `libs/csharp/Rasm.Materials/AGENTS.md`, `libs/csharp/AGENTS.md`, `.claude/skills/coding-csharp/SKILL.md`, and relevant source-standard docs before edits.

## Boundary

- `Rasm.Materials.csproj` intentionally has zero `ProjectReference`.
- Keep Materials sibling to `Rasm`, `Rasm.Rhino`, and `Rasm.Grasshopper`, not subordinate to geometry or host code.
- Never add Rhino, Grasshopper, geometry kernel, JSON, SQL, source-generator, native-binary, or I/O awareness.
- Downstream consumer libraries compose `Rasm.Materials` with geometry or host boundaries by referencing both sides.

## Catalogue Shape

- Build one polymorphic query surface per material folder.
- Attach canonical payloads to closed `[SmartEnum]` vocabularies and Thinktecture unions.
- Author data directly in C#; the type system is the schema.
- Keep catalogue records immutable and metric-first; convert imperial standards at authoring time.
- Encode source standards as typed records or unions, not string notes.

## Bricks

- `Bricks/` owns regional brick sizes, bond patterns, special shapes, joint profiles, regional masonry policy, coring archetypes, arch rules, and scalar brick assemblies.
- Add bricks by extending `BrickDesignation`; do not fork regional taxonomies into separate enums.
- Model bonds as data plus interpreter through course templates, orientations, and offset fractions.
- Keep brick-owned layout scalar: course, station, elevation, angle, and policy records only.

## Extension Rules

- Future catalogue libraries such as `Rasm.Standards` or `Rasm.Codes` follow the same zero-reference sibling doctrine.
- Future material folders get their own namespace, catalogue, query surface, and error union.
- Do not share cross-material records merely because names overlap; each material owns its domain semantics.
